title: Tickle under center gets Ore. high school QB suspended
text:

(Photo: Photo: Brent Drinkut/Statesman Journal) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
SALEM, Ore. (AP) - An Oregon high school quarterback has been suspended from school because officials said he inappropriately touched another player during practice. 
West Salem High principal Ken Phillips declined to discuss the incident, but freshman quarterback Garrett Moore told the Statesman Journal it happened when he was taking snaps under center last week. 
He said he inadvertently tickled the center while moving his hands. He said the center later kneed him in the crotch. 
Moore says an assistant principal called him in for a pair of meetings Tuesday and gave him a three-day suspension. A written notice says it's for inappropriately touching another student during practice. 
His mother, Tamara Moore, says the situation is absurd and she plans to appeal the suspension. Read or Share this story: http://on.kgw.com/1LlQhfX TOP VIDEOS
